Words 2001-2100

  1. practise
    She wants to practise her English every day.

  2. praise
    The teacher gave praise to the students for their hard work.

  3. pray
    They pray for good health and happiness.

  4. prayer
    The prayer was short but meaningful.

  5. predict
    Can you predict what will happen next?

  6. prediction
    His prediction about the weather was correct.

  7. prefer
    I prefer tea over coffee.

  8. pregnant
    She is pregnant with her first child.

  9. preparation
    Good preparation is key to success.

  10. prepare
    We need to prepare for the meeting tomorrow.

  11. prepared
    She was well prepared for the exam.

  12. presence
    His presence made the event more special.

  13. present
    She gave a present to her best friend.

  14. presentation
    The presentation was clear and easy to follow.

  15. preserve
    We must preserve the environment for future generations.

  16. president
    The president gave a speech to the nation.

  17. press
    Press the button to start the machine.

  18. pressure
    The pressure to succeed can be overwhelming.

  19. pretend
    The children pretend to be superheroes.

  20. pretty
    The flowers in the garden are very pretty.

  21. prevent
    We must act now to prevent further damage.

  22. previous
    I liked the previous version of the book better.

  23. previously
    She had previously worked as a teacher.

  24. price
    The price of the book is very reasonable.

  25. priest
    The priest led the ceremony in the church.

  26. primary
    Education is a primary need for every child.

  27. prime
    This is the prime example of teamwork.

  28. prince
    The prince visited the village to meet the people.

  29. princess
    The princess wore a beautiful dress to the ball.

  30. principle
    Honesty is a key principle in life.

  31. print
    Please print the document for the meeting.

  32. printer
    The printer is out of paper again.

  33. printing
    The printing of the book will take a week.

  34. priority
    Safety is our top priority.

  35. prison
    He was sent to prison for his crimes.

  36. prisoner
    The prisoner escaped during the night.

  37. privacy
    Everyone has the right to privacy.

  38. private
    This is a private conversation.

  39. prize
    She won a prize for her excellent performance.

  40. probably
    It will probably rain later today.

  41. problem
    We need to solve this problem quickly.

  42. procedure
    Follow the procedure carefully to avoid mistakes.

  43. process
    The process of making bread takes time.

  44. produce
    Farmers produce fresh vegetables for the market.

  45. producer
    The producer is responsible for the success of the movie.

  46. product
    This product is very popular among young people.

  47. production
    The production of the new car model has started.

  48. profession
    Teaching is a noble profession.

  49. professional
    She is a professional photographer.

  50. professor
    The professor explained the topic in detail.

  51. profile
    Update your profile with the latest information.

  52. profit
    The company made a huge profit this year.

  53. program
    The program will start at 7 PM.

  54. programme
    The TV programme was very interesting.

  55. progress
    She is making good progress in her studies.

  56. project
    The team is working on a new project.

  57. promise
    He made a promise to help her.

  58. promote
    The company plans to promote its new product.

  59. pronounce
    Can you pronounce this word correctly?

  60. proof
    We need proof to support the claim.

  61. proper
    Wear proper clothes for the occasion.

  62. properly
    Make sure the machine is working properly.

  63. property
    This property belongs to my family.

  64. proposal
    The proposal was accepted by the committee.

  65. propose
    He plans to propose a new idea at the meeting.

  66. prospect
    The prospect of a holiday excites me.

  67. protect
    We must protect our natural resources.

  68. protection
    The law provides protection for endangered animals.

  69. protest
    The workers held a protest against low wages.

  70. proud
    She is proud of her achievements.

  71. prove
    Can you prove that your statement is true?

  72. provide
    The school will provide free books to students.

  73. psychologist
    The psychologist helped him deal with his anxiety.

  74. psychology
    She is studying psychology at university.

  75. pub
    They went to the pub to relax after work.

  76. public
    The park is open to the public.

  77. publication
    The publication of the book was delayed.

  78. publish
    The author plans to publish her new novel soon.

  79. pull
    Pull the door to open it.

  80. punish
    The teacher decided to punish the student for cheating.

  81. punishment
    The punishment for the crime was severe.

  82. pupil
    The pupil asked a question during the lesson.

  83. purchase
    She decided to purchase a new laptop.

  84. pure
    The water from the spring is pure and clean.

  85. purple
    She wore a purple dress to the party.

  86. purpose
    The purpose of the meeting is to discuss the project.

  87. pursue
    He decided to pursue a career in medicine.

  88. push
    Push the door to enter the room.

  89. put
    Please put the book on the table.

  90. qualification
    She has the qualification needed for the job.

  91. qualified
    He is highly qualified for the position.

  92. qualify
    She worked hard to qualify for the competition.

  93. quality
    The quality of the product is excellent.

  94. quantity
    We need a large quantity of paper for the project.

  95. quarter
    The game will start in the first quarter of the year.

  96. queen
    The queen visited the city during her tour.

  97. question
    Do you have a question about the topic?

  98. queue
    We had to wait in a long queue to buy tickets.

  99. quick
    She gave a quick answer to the question.

  100. quickly
    He quickly finished his homework before dinner.
